    • Method Detail

      • getNameHistory

        public static java.lang.String[] getNameHistory(java.util.UUID uuid)
        This will return a string array with the name history of the user, where the last element is the current name. Caching is not implemented!
        Parameters:
        uuid - the UUID of the user to check for
        Returns:
        a String[] array with the name history. Can be null if an error happens!

      • getUUID

        public static java.util.UUID getUUID(java.lang.String username)
        This will get the UUID for the username on Mojang's API. Note that this will only return a UUID, if the player's account exists in the Mojang database aka. they bought the game. Caching is not implemented!
        Parameters:
        username - the username of the player
        Returns:
        the UUID of such player (can be null!)
